    <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1"/>
    <p>
     BOY-FRIEND:
     <br/>
     Some people do the full movement for the sign "friend" when signing "boyfriend" 
but my suggestion is to treat this sign like a typical compound sign and drop 
the second movement in the sign "friend."
     <br/>
     <br/>
     BOYFRIEND (compound):
    </p>
    <p>
     <img border="0" height="480" src="../../signjpegs/f/boyfriend-compound-01.jpg" width="480"/>
     <img border="0" height="480" src="../../signjpegs/f/boyfriend-compound-02.jpg" width="480"/>
     <img border="0" height="480" src="../../signjpegs/f/boyfriend-compound-03.jpg" width="480"/>
     <img border="0" height="480" src="../../signjpegs/f/boyfriend-compound-04.jpg" width="480"/>
    </p>
    <p>
     BOYFRIEND (full version):
    </p>
    <p>
     <iframe allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="315" name="I2" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/EHkYHDKBm5Y?rel=0" width="560">
